{{italic title}}
'''''Body Pressure''''' is a 1974 [[performance art|performance piece]] by [[United States|American]] artist [[Bruce Nauman]]. The performer is instructed to press their body against a wall in various positions; Nauman says that it "may become a very erotic exercise".<ref>Bruce Nauman, ''[http://www.e-flux.com/projects/do_it/manuals/artists/n/N001/N001A_text.html Body Pressure] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070927222153/http://www.e-flux.com/projects/do_it/manuals/artists/n/N001/N001A_text.html# |date=2007-09-27 }}'', 1974. [http://www.e-flux.com/ e-flux], 2002.</ref>

The piece was re-interpreted and performed by [[Marina Abramović]] as part of her ''[[Seven Easy Pieces]]'' in 2005.<ref>Sean Kelly Gallery, "[http://www.seveneasypieces.com/7easyperformances/november92005.html]", 2005.</ref>

